Architecture MVP


Short architecture description

Application consists of three modules:

Model - module which is responsible for different operations with data, such as downloading data from internet, saving data to database 
and retrieving it. This module contains of classes for creating database and working with it with use of Room library, classes for tuning 
Retrofit and working with GitHub API, POJO class, that is using during parsing API response and during saving/retrieving data from DB.

View - module wherein occurs all kind of actions relative to UI - initializing views, showing to user loading and error messages, showing 
detailed information about repository etc.

Presenter - module which uses previous two modules in general app work
